I"ؗ<blockquote>
  <p>The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">has_type</code> relation is good but doesn’t give us a <em>executable algorithm</em> – 不是一个算法
but it’s <em>syntax directed</em>, just one typing rule for one term (unique typing) – translate into function!</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="comparing-types">Comparing Types</h2>

<p>首先我们需要 check equality for types.
这里非常简单，如果是 SystemF 会麻烦很多，对 <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">∀</code> 要做 local nameless 或者 alpha renaming:</p>

<div class="language-coq highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">Fixpoint</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="no">eqb_ty</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">(</span><span class="no">T1</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="no">T2</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="no">ty</span><span class="o">)</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="no">bool</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p">:</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w">
